        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>MADRID • La Liga pres­i­dent Javier Te­bas has warned a break­away Euro­pean Su­per League would not be in the long-term in­ter­ests of clubs, a day af­ter Real Madrid chief Florentino Perez spoke of an ur­gent need to re­form cur­rent com­pe­ti­tions to “en­sure football re­mains at­trac­tive”.</p>
    <p>Hit­ting back at Perez, Te­bas said on Mon­day that the of­ten talked about pro­posal is a “per­fect project to go bank­rupt” and is “un­fea­si­ble”.</p>


